text: Tatiana Markushevskaya (born 1 June 1994) is a Belarusian footballer who plays as a midfielder and has appeared for the Belarus women's national team. ==Career== Markushevskaya has been capped for the Belarus national team, appearing for the team during the 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup qualifying cycle. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Belarusian women's footballers Category:Belarus women's international footballers Category:Women's association football midfielders
